review_blob: I was surprised how much I liked this. For a big company brew it has a lot to offer. Sweet summertime aroma that reminds of a mix of stone fruits (peaches and apricots) and the flavor has a nice mix of the same stone fruit flavors and hops. Finished a little weak but at least doesnt have that died in your mouth aftertaste of some mass produced IPAs
Great for the summer. Nice session beer, low abv and crisp taste makes it easy drinking. Its what mass produced light beers whish they were
